# Migration files MUST be byte-identical on every machine.
#
# drizzle records an applied migration as the sha256 of its file CONTENTS. This repo is
# developed on Windows with core.autocrlf=true, so without this rule a checkout would rewrite
# these files to CRLF locally while the Linux CI runner and the container see LF -- different
# bytes, different hash, and an already-applied migration would look PENDING. It would then be
# re-run, hit "relation already exists", and fail the initContainer (safely, but the deploy
# stops dead and the cause is invisible).
#
# Pinning eol=lf makes the hash stable across Windows, CI, and the image.
# NOTE the leading `**/`: a gitattributes pattern containing a slash is anchored to the
# directory holding this file, so plain `drizzle/**` would only match a repo-ROOT drizzle/ and
# silently miss api/drizzle/ -- which is exactly where these live. Verify with:
#   git check-attr text eol -- api/drizzle/0000_natural_morlocks.sql
**/drizzle/**/*.sql text eol=lf
**/drizzle/**/*.json text eol=lf
